---
description: Pragmatic pre-commit code review over current working-tree uncommitted changes with maintainability-first priorities
alwaysApply: false
---

Use this rule when the user asks for code review, pre-commit review, or review of current changes.

Supported scope classes:
- working-tree uncommitted changes
- staged changes
- other explicitly requested ranges

Default behavior:
- review current working-tree uncommitted changes
- inspect staged changes with `git diff --cached`
- inspect unstaged tracked changes with `git diff`
- include untracked files when relevant and readable
- if nothing is changed, say that clearly in Chinese and stop

